		<sect1 id="base-plate">
			<title id="title-base-plate">Housing Base-plate</title>
			<para>The Housing Base-plate is comprised of two materials:</para>
			<itemizedlist spacing="compact">
				<listitem>
					<para>Aluminum Tread plate</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>Chip Board</para>
				</listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
			<para>Using the measurements in the following diagram, follow the procedures below.</para>
			<figure>
				<title>Housing Base-Plate (First Angle)</title>
				<mediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="../images/base-plate.png" format="PNG"/>
					</imageobject>
				</mediaobject>
			</figure>
			<procedure>
				<title>Building the Housing Base-Plate</title>
				<step>
					<para>Create the basic shape.</para>
					<substeps>
						<step>
							<para>Cut materials into a rectangle of width 1055 mm, length 950
							mm.</para>
						</step>
						<step>
							<para>From the center point draw an arc across one edge of the
							width.</para>
						</step>
						<step>
							<para>Cut away excess material to form the curved edge.</para>
						</step>
					</substeps>
				</step>
				<step>
					<para>Create the hole in the tread plate.</para>
					<substeps>
						<step>
							<para>Draw a line 50mm from the straight edge along the width.</para>
						</step>
						<step>
							<para>Draw a line 227.5mm from the straight edge along the width.</para>
						</step>
						<step>
							<para>Draw a line 405mm from the straight edge along the width.</para>
						</step>
						<step>
							<para>Draw a line 355mm on each side of the width center-line along the
								length.</para>
						</step>
						<step>
							<para>Draw a line 525mm on each side of the width center-line along the
								length.</para>
							<para>You should see a rectangle.</para>
						</step>
						<step>
							<para>Use the intersection where the line at 227.5mm crosses the two
								355mm lines, draw arcs on each end and inside the borders of the
								marked rectangle.</para>
						</step>
						<step>
							<para>Cut away the center shape.</para>
						</step>
					</substeps>
				</step>
				<step>
					<para>Secure the tread plate to the chip board using contact glue and
						pop-rivets.</para>
					<substeps>
						<step>
							<para>Match the basic shape and bond the tread plate on top of the chip
								board.</para>
						</step>
						<step>
							<para>Drill a hole through the tread plate around the edge at the top of
								the arc, each corner and at the edge-points where the arch and
								straight edges meet.</para>
						</step>
						<step>
							<para>From the tread plate side, insert a pop-rivet into each
							hole.</para>
						</step>
					</substeps>
				</step>
			</procedure>
			<tip>
				<para>Instead of cutting by hand using a circular saw, use a laser cutting
				tool.</para>
			</tip>
		</sect1>
